UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2020, more girls and boys are enrolled, retained and learning in pre-primary and primary schools, and there are fewer children out of school.

description.narrative: Over one million children at primary and secondary levels benefitted from new learning materials with UNICEF support in 2020.;UNICEF;adapted to the COVID-19 context;to achieve results;by supporting alternative mechanisms to deliver learning content (radio broadcasts, distribution of self-learning booklets),;ensuring learning continuation;for over 635,000 lower secondary school students.;UNICEF;also;provided technical support to;the Ministry of Education;for;the development of curriculum and assessment mechanisms, resulting in the;production of;the;first;national curricula;documents to be piloted since 2012.;The COVID-19 context did limit;the possibility of teacher;supervision;and training of;school directors. | Status:Met | As-of Date:12/01/2021
